exiftool.ImageFileCharacteristics: No relocs, Executable, No line numbers, No symbols, Large address aware

threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This sample is a backdoor/downloader. It collects system information including the computer name, username, OS version, and MAC address. This data is then exfiltrated to a hardcoded Command and Control (C2) server. The malware can receive commands from the C2, notably a 'download' command which triggers it to drop a VBScript downloader to disk and execute it to fetch and run a secondary payload. The communication with the C2 is XOR-encrypted.
